---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const breadcrumbs = [
  { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
  { name: 'Workflows', url: '/workflows' },
  { name: 'Marketplace', url: '/workflows/marketplace' }
];

const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'How is this different from other breeder listings?',
    answer: 'BreederHQ Marketplace is connected to actual breeding program data. Verification badges are earned through documented health testing, not self-reported claims. Buyers see real data, not marketing.'
  },
  {
    question: 'What are verification badges?',
    answer: 'Badges indicate verified achievements like "Health Tested Program," "Pedigree Documented," or "Established Breeder." They\'re earned automatically when your records meet the criteria, so there is no manual application needed.'
  },
  {
    question: 'What kinds of listings can I create?',
    answer: 'Three types: individual animal listings (animals available for sale or adoption), offspring group listings (litters, foals, kids, lambs, kits), and program or service listings (stud services, guardian homes, trained animals, rehoming, co-ownership). You choose which types to use.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Do I have to list all my animals?',
    answer: 'No. You control exactly which animals are visible on the marketplace. Keep your program private or make it public, and you decide for each animal individually.'
  },
  {
    question: 'How do inquiries work?',
    answer: 'Buyer inquiries come directly to your BreederHQ dashboard. You can respond, qualify leads, and manage all communications in one place alongside your other client management.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Can I find stud services or breeding partners for my own animals?',
    answer: 'Yes. The marketplace doubles as a cross-network search for breeders. Filter by species, breed, health test results, color genetics, COI, and location to find genetically compatible matches across the entire BreederHQ community.'
  },
  {
    question: 'What does it cost to list?',
    answer: 'Animal listings are a one-time fee based on species, with no monthly charges and no commissions on sales. All listing fees are currently waived during our early access period.'
  }
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Breeder Marketplace Connected to Your Records | BreederHQ"
  description="Get discovered by serious buyers. List individual animals, offspring groups, and stud or program services. Verification badges earned from real health testing data, plus cross-network matching across the entire BreederHQ community."
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
  faqs={faqs}
>
  <a href="#main-content" class="skip-link sr-only focus:not-sr-only focus:absolute focus:top-4 focus:left-4 focus:z-50 focus:px-4 focus:py-2 focus:bg-white focus:text-black focus:shadow-lg focus:rounded">
    Skip to content
  </a>

  <main id="main-content">
  <nav class="breadcrumb py-4 px-4 bg-gray-50" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
    <ol class="flex items-center space-x-2 max-w-4xl mx-auto text-sm">
      <li><a href="/" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Home</a></li>
      <li class="text-gray-400">›</li>
      <li><a href="/workflows" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Workflows</a></li>
      <li class="text-gray-400">›</li>
      <li aria-current="page" class="text-gray-600">Marketplace</li>
    </ol>
  </nav>

  <!-- Section 1: What This Page Is About -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold mb-6">Get Discovered by Serious Buyers</h1>

      <aside class="tldr-box bg-gray-100 border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] p-6 my-8 rounded" role="complementary" aria-label="Page summary">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">TL;DR</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          The BreederHQ Marketplace connects responsible breeders with educated buyers. List individual animals, offspring groups (litters, foals, kids, lambs, kits), and program or stud service offerings. Verification badges are earned through documented health testing, not self-reported claims, and you can search the entire BreederHQ network for genetically compatible matches. Your reputation is visible, verifiable, and valuable.
        </p>
      </aside>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        Quality breeders can struggle to stand out online. Volume operations dominate search results. Undocumented breeders undercut prices. Serious buyers can't easily tell the difference. The BreederHQ Marketplace changes that by putting verified program data front and center.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 2: Why Breeders Search for This -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Why finding the right buyers is hard</h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Good breeders face constant challenges:
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-3 text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Generic listing sites treat responsible breeders the same as puppy mills</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Your health testing investment doesn't translate to visibility</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Buyers can't verify claims, so they don't trust anyone</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Price shoppers waste your time with inquiries they'll never follow through</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Your website doesn't rank against sites with bigger marketing budgets</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Word of mouth is slow and unpredictable</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        Doing the right thing should give you a competitive advantage. Usually it doesn't.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 3: How Breeders Usually Handle It -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">How breeders try to get discovered</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Personal websites</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            You build a website, write about your program, post photos. But SEO is competitive. Your site ranks page 10 while questionable breeders dominate page 1.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Generic listing sites</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Sites like PuppyFind, NextDayPets, DreamHorse, EquineNow, breed-specific classifieds, and Craigslist. Anyone can list, there is no verification, and your documented program sits right next to volume ads.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Social media</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Facebook groups, Instagram. Good for community, but algorithms limit reach. Building an audience takes years of consistent content.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Breed club referrals</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Registry referral lists. Trusted but limited reach. Most buyers don't know to look there.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Word of mouth</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Happy clients refer friends. The best leads, but you can't control the volume or timing.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 4: Where That Breaks Down -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Where those approaches stretch thin</h2>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">No easy way to prove quality</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Every listing claims "health tested" and "raised with love." Buyers have no quick way to verify any of it, so they end up skeptical of everyone, including you.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Documented programs look the same as the rest</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            On generic listing sites, a responsible breeder's ad looks identical to a volume operation's. Sometimes worse, because volume operations invest heavily in professional photos and copy.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Price becomes the default differentiator</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            When buyers can't evaluate quality at a glance, they shop on price. Your fully health-tested, documented animal loses to a cheaper "no papers" listing every time.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Unqualified inquiries eat your time</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Inquiries from people who want an animal tomorrow, don't want to fill out an application, or can't afford your pricing add up fast. Hours spent on leads that were never going to convert.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Reputation isn't portable</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Your Facebook reviews don't show up on your website. Your OFA, PennHIP, or genetic panel results aren't visible on listing sites. Your reputation is scattered across platforms and hard to verify.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Marketing takes time you don't have</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            You're busy with actual breeding work. Social media management, SEO, content creation: full-time jobs on top of the full-time job you already have.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 5: What a Correct System Looks Like -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">What it looks like when your records are connected to your listings</h2>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Verify claims with real data</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-lg text-gray-700">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Health testing badges backed by actual test records</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Pedigree verification from documented lineage</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Program history visible (years breeding, litters produced)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Buyers see proof, not promises</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Surface quality programs</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-lg text-gray-700">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Breeders with verified health testing rank higher</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Documented programs get more visibility</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Investment in quality translates to marketplace advantage</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>No pay-to-play advertising that lets anyone buy the top spot</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Attract educated buyers</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-lg text-gray-700">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Buyers who understand why health testing matters</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>People willing to wait for the right match</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Families who value transparency and documentation</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Fewer tire-kickers, more serious inquiries</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Cross-network matching for breeders</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-lg text-gray-700">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Search for genetically compatible matches across the entire BreederHQ network</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Filter by species, breed, health results, color genetics, COI, and location</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Discover stud services, program offerings, and co-ownership opportunities</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Reach out directly through the same inquiry system your own buyers use</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Integrated inquiry management</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-lg text-gray-700">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Inquiries flow directly into your management system</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Qualify, respond, and track leads in one place</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>No separate inbox to check</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Communication history preserved</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Control over visibility</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-lg text-gray-700">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Choose which animals to list</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Set your program's public profile</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Hide or show based on availability</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="mr-3">•</span>
              <span>Your data, your decisions</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 6: How BreederHQ Supports This -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4 bg-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] text-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">BreederHQ Marketplace rewards responsible breeding</h2>

      <p class="text-xl leading-relaxed mb-8">
        Your health testing records become verification badges. Your documented pedigrees prove lineage. Your program history shows experience. Buyers see real data, not marketing claims. Quality breeders finally get the visibility they deserve.
      </p>

      <p class="text-xl leading-relaxed mb-8">
        Inquiries arrive in your dashboard alongside your other client management. One system for breeding records, client relationships, and marketplace presence.
      </p>

      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
        <a href="https://accounts.breederhq.com/register?intent=breeder_dashboard" class="inline-block bg-white text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-bold text-lg hover:bg-gray-100 transition text-center" style="min-height: 44px;">
          Get Started Free
        </a>
        <a href="/workflows/waitlists-and-placement" class="inline-block bg-transparent border-2 border-white text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-bold text-lg hover:bg-white hover:text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] transition text-center" style="min-height: 44px;">
          See waitlist management →
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 7: Who This Is For -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Built for breeders who:</h2>

      <ul class="space-y-3 text-lg text-gray-700">
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Invest in health testing and want it to matter</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Document their breeding program properly</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Want to reach buyers who value quality over price</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Are tired of competing with volume operations on generic sites</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Don't have time for aggressive marketing</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Want their reputation to be visible and verifiable</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Want to search the BreederHQ network for compatible stud services or breeding partners</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 8: Who This Is Not For -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">This probably isn't for you if:</h2>

      <ul class="space-y-3 text-lg text-gray-700 mb-8">
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>You don't do structured health testing</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>You prefer to keep your program completely private</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <span class="mr-3">•</span>
          <span>Your waitlist is already full through word of mouth</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        The marketplace is built to highlight documented, verifiable programs. If that matches how you work, it helps you stand out. If not, BreederHQ is still here for the rest of your operation when you're ready.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 9: FAQ -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4 faq-section">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-12">Frequently asked questions</h2>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>How is this different from other breeder listings?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>BreederHQ Marketplace is connected to actual breeding program data. Verification badges are earned through documented health testing, not self-reported claims. Buyers see real data, not marketing.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>What are verification badges?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Badges indicate verified achievements like "Health Tested Program," "Pedigree Documented," or "Established Breeder." They're earned automatically when your records meet the criteria, so there is no manual application needed.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>What kinds of listings can I create?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Three types: individual animal listings (animals available for sale or adoption), offspring group listings (litters, foals, kids, lambs, kits), and program or service listings (stud services, guardian homes, trained animals, rehoming, co-ownership). You choose which types to use.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>Do I have to list all my animals?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>No. You control exactly which animals are visible on the marketplace. Keep your program private or make it public, and you decide for each animal individually.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>How do inquiries work?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Buyer inquiries come directly to your BreederHQ dashboard. You can respond, qualify leads, and manage all communications in one place alongside your other client management.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>Can I find stud services or breeding partners for my own animals?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Yes. The marketplace doubles as a cross-network search for breeders. Filter by species, breed, health test results, color genetics, COI, and location to find genetically compatible matches across the entire BreederHQ community.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          <span>What does it cost to list?</span>
          <svg class="faq-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Animal listings are a one-time fee based on species, with no monthly charges and no commissions on sales. All listing fees are currently waived during our early access period.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 10: Related Resources -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Learn more</h2>
